e-only research without marking the limitation\",\n    \"rebuilding auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, or design system without ADR approval\",\n    \"declaring iOS validation complete without macOS or GitHub Actions evidence\",\n    \"skipping Appium exploratory evidence unless allow_macos_deferred is explicit\"\n  ]\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_7","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' .workflow/iphone-app-factory/adr.md\"","aggregated_output":"# ADR-001: WakeTask on SwiftAIBoilerplatePro\n\n## Status\nAccepted\n\n## Date\n2026-05-14\n\n## Context\nWakeTask must ship as a differentiated, reliability-first alarm experience while meeting:\n- Spec requirements (`FR-01..FR-06`, `NFR-01..NFR-06`)\n- Definition of Done gates (`DoD-01..DoD-18`)\n- Quality bar constraints, including mandatory boilerplate reuse and App Store 4.3 hardening.\n\nThe quality bar explicitly forbids rebuilding platform modules (auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, design system, DI/composition root) without explicit ADR justification.\n\n## Decision\nAdopt an extension-first architecture on `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` with no module removals.\n\n### Module decisions\n- Keep and extend: `Packages/Core`, `Packages/Storage`, `Packages/AI`, `Packages/FeatureSettings`, `Packages/Localization`, `Packages/DesignSystem`, `CompositionRoot`, `Config/App.xcconfig`.\n- Keep with minimal/no MVP change: `Packages/Networking`, `Packages/Auth`, `Packages/Payments`, `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj`.\n- Removed modules: none.\n\n## Dependency Order\n1. `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj` + `Config/App.xcconfig` set build/runtime configuration.\n2. `Packages/Core` defines WakeTask domain and use-case contracts.\n3. `Packages/Storage` / `Packages/Networking` provide adapter implementations for repositories and external I/O.\n4. `Packages/AI` provides mission adaptation policies consumed by Core use-cases.\n5. `Packages/Auth` / `Packages/Payments` remain optional capability modules, not wake-path prerequisites.\n6. `Packages/FeatureSettings` and `Packages/Localization` supply runtime policy and copy for feature surfaces.\n7. `Packages/DesignSystem` supplies accessible UI primitives.\n8. `CompositionRoot` assembles dependency graph and routes app flows.\n\n## Rationale\n- Meets “extend before replace” contract and avoids schedule risk from platform rewrites.\n- Preserves tested package boundaries and CI setup already aligned to iOS quality gates.\n- Keeps critical wake path local-first and reliable while allowing optional integrations.\n- Supports App Store 4.3 differentiation by concentrating effort in product-specific behavior (ledger, wake contract, adaptive mission rotation, first-task bridge) rather than commodity infrastructure rebuild.\n\n## App Store 4.3 Consequences\n- Positive with this decision: differentiation is explicit in user-visible behavior (`D-01..D-04`) and not diluted by template-level reimplementation work.\n- If modules were removed/rebuilt without necessity:\n  - delivery risk increases, reducing confidence in polishing unique UX proof points;\n  - product can appear as a generic alarm clone with infrastructure churn but weak user-facing differentiation;\n  - review narrative weakens because custom work is not clearly tied to unique WakeTask outcomes.\n\nBecause no modules are removed, there is no dependency breakage introduced by this ADR.\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n- Full custom app architecture replacing boilerplate modules.\n  - Rejected: violates quality-bar default, increases risk/cost, weakens overnight delivery confidence.\n- Hybrid partial rebuild of selected infra modules.\n  - Rejected: insufficient value for MVP compared with extending current modules.\n\n## Verification Impact\nThis ADR requires:\n- architecture mapping in `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`.\n- CI evidence for build/test/lint/format/secret scan.\n- Appium exploratory evidence and 4.3 hardening checks before release handoff.\n- Appium deferral is not permitted for this run: allow_macos_deferred=false; missing hosted macOS CI simulator evidence blocks release handoff.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
