{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_12","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-iphone/Config/Secrets.example.xcconfig\"","aggregated_output":"// Copy this file to Config/Secrets.xcconfig and fill these values.\n// See supabase/DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md for setup instructions\n\n// Supabase Configuration\n// Get these from: https://app.supabase.com → Project Settings → API\nSUPABASE_URL = https://YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co\nSUPABASE_ANON_KEY = YOUR_PUBLIC_ANON_KEY\n\n// Google Sign In (Optional)\n// Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com → APIs & Services → Credentials\n// Create iOS OAuth Client ID, then paste the client ID here\n// GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID = YOUR_IOS_CLIENT_ID.apps.googleusercontent.com\n\n// RevenueCat Configuration  \n// Get from: https://app.revenuecat.com → Project Settings → API Keys\nREVENUECAT_API_KEY = YOUR_RC_KEY\nRC_ENTITLEMENT_ID = pro\n\n// AI Proxy Configuration (Supabase Edge Function)\n// After deploying the Edge Function, use: https://YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co/functions/v1\nPROXY_BASE_URL = https://YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co/functions/v1\nPROXY_PATH = /ai\n\n// OneSignal Push Notifications (Optional)\n// Get from: https://onesignal.com → Settings → Keys & IDs\n// Leave commented out if you don't want push notifications\n// See docs/integrations/OneSignal.md for setup guide\nONESIGNAL_APP_ID = YOUR_ONESIGNAL_APP_ID\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_15","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Resources/terms.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Terms of Service\n\n**Last Updated:** May 14, 2026\n\n## 1. Agreement\nBy using WakeTask, you agree to these Terms.\n\n## 2. Service Description\nWakeTask provides alarm, wake mission, wake-check, and reliability tracking tools intended to help users wake and start first-task execution.\n\n## 3. Accounts\nYou are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for activity on your account.\n\n## 4. Subscriptions and Billing\nPaid features may require a subscription. Subscriptions renew automatically unless canceled at least 24 hours before renewal, subject to Apple billing rules.\n\n## 5. Acceptable Use\nYou agree not to misuse the app, attempt to disrupt service operation, reverse engineer restricted components, or violate applicable law.\n\n## 6. Availability\nWakeTask may be updated, changed, or suspended. Alarm reliability depends on device state, permissions, and OS behavior.\n\n## 7. Disclaimer\nThe app is provided \"as is\" without warranties of uninterrupted operation or fitness for a particular purpose.\n\n## 8. Limitation of Liability\nTo the maximum extent permitted by law, WakeTask and its operators are not liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages.\n\n## 9. Termination\nWe may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms.\n\n## 10. Changes to Terms\nWe may update these Terms. Continued use after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.\n\n## 11. Contact\nFor support and legal inquiries: `support@waketask.app`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/BrandConfig.swift\"","aggregated_output":"import SwiftUI\n\n/// Brand configuration for customization\n/// \n/// Buyers can modify these values to customize the app's branding.\n/// Changes here will be reflected throughout the app.\npublic struct BrandConfig {\n    \n    /// App display name shown in UI\n    public static let appDisplayName = \"WakeTask\"\n    \n    /// Accent color for highlights and CTAs\n    public static let accentColor: Color = DSColors.primary\n    \n    /// SF Symbol name for default avatar\n    public static let avatarFallbackSymbol = \"person.circle.fill\"\n    \n    /// App icon background color (for generated icons)\n    public static let appIconBackground: Color = DSColors.primary\n    \n    // MARK: - Customization Guide\n    \n    /*\n     HOW TO CUSTOMIZE YOUR BRAND\n     ============================\n     \n     1. App Display Name:\n        Change `appDisplayName` to your app's name\n        Example: \"MyAI Assistant\" or \"ChatBot Pro\"\n     \n     2. Accent Color:\n        Option A: Update the Primary color in Colors.xcassets\n        Option B: Set accentColor to a custom Color:\n            public static let accentColor = Color(red: 0.2, green: 0.6, blue: 1.0)\n     \n     3. Avatar Symbol:\n        Browse SF Symbols app and pick an icon:\n        Examples: \"sparkles\", \"brain.head.profile\", \"message.fill\"\n        Update `avatarFallbackSymbol` with the symbol name\n     \n     4. Color Scheme:\n        Edit Resources/Colors.xcassets to customize:\n        - Primary (brand color)\n        - BubbleUser (user message bubble)\n        - BubbleAssistant (AI message bubble)\n        - TextPrimary, TextSecondary (text colors)\n        - Background, Separator\n     \n     5. Typography:\n        Modify DSTypography in Typography.swift:\n        - Change font sizes\n        - Switch font design (.default, .rounded, .serif, .monospaced)\n        - Adjust line spacing\n     \n     All changes automatically apply throughout the app with no additional code changes needed.\n     */\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Resources/privacy.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Privacy Policy\n\n**Last Updated:** May 14, 2026\n\n## Overview\nWakeTask helps users reliably wake up by running alarms, wake missions, and post-dismiss wake checks.\n\n## Data We Collect\n- Account information you provide (such as email when you create an account).\n- Alarm and wake-flow configuration (alarm times, strictness, mission preferences, first-task setup).\n- Reliability activity records (trigger events, mission completion, wake-check outcomes, escalation outcomes).\n- Subscription status and purchase entitlement state.\n- Basic diagnostic events needed to keep the app stable.\n\n## How We Use Data\n- Deliver alarm and wake verification functionality.\n- Show your reliability timeline and weekly consistency summaries.\n- Maintain account access, sync features (when enabled), and subscription access.\n- Detect errors and improve reliability/performance.\n\n## Mission Validation and Sensors\nFor MVP, wake mission validation is processed on-device where possible. WakeTask does not use ad SDK interruptions in the critical wake path.\n\n## Data Sharing\n- Service providers we use to operate the app (for example: authentication, payments, and infrastructure).\n- Legal disclosure when required by law.\n\nWe do not sell your personal information.\n\n## Retention\nWe retain data as long as needed to provide the service, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements.\n\n## Your Choices\n- You can request account deletion.\n- You can request access to your stored data.\n- You can manage notification permissions in iOS Settings.\n\n## Security\nWe use reasonable safeguards including encrypted transport and platform security controls, but no system is guaranteed 100% secure.\n\n## Children\nWakeTask is not directed to children under 13.\n\n## Contact\nFor privacy questions: `privacy@waketask.app`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
